raw_data.title: Junior Program Manager
raw_data.description: The Junior Program Manager leads multiple crews of structured cable plant installers.  Demonstrates the proper procedures for installing, terminating, testing, troubleshooting and documenting a cable plant system to team members. Provides Quality Assurance inspections to ensure work is performed according to industry standards and codes. Generates project equipment lists and bills of material. Interacts daily with customers as required, and informs Project Manager of potential risks, issues, or changes in the scope of work. Is capable of overseeing all aspects of structured cabling design and installation services for a staff of Junior, Mid and Senior Technicians.
raw_data.required_certifications_or_licenses: OSHA 10-Hour Training; OEM Certification(s) for design and installation

raw_data.title: Junior Technician
raw_data.description: The Junior Technician is a cable technician capable of following instructions and adapting as a member in the field. Demonstrates the proper procedures for installing, terminating, testing, troubleshooting and documenting a cable plant system to team members. Adheres to Quality inspections to ensure his work is performed according to industry standards and codes.

raw_data.title: Mid Technician
raw_data.description: The Mid Technician is capable of functioning on their own in a team environment. Demonstrates the proper procedures for installing, terminating, testing, troubleshooting and documenting a cable plant system for designated projects. Adheres to Quality inspections to ensure his work is performed according to industry standards and codes.
raw_data.required_certifications_or_licenses: BICSI Level-100 Installer or OEM Equivalent
